<node id="ASSET RESTRUCTURING">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">Asset restructuring is a significant event that various entities have undergone, contributing to their growth, success, and improvement in operational efficiency. Examples of such events include Buildcorp Holdings reorganizing its assets, leading to growth and success, Capital Finance Group's asset restructuring in December 2018 to improve operational efficiency and increase company value, CleanCo's optimization of its business structure and operational efficiency in August, EduCorp's restructuring prior to strategic acquisitions, Elevate Retail Inc.'s restructuring involving closing underperforming stores and reallocating resources for improved efficiency and increased company value in April 2020, Entertainment Enterprises Inc.'s restructuring to focus on core entertainment businesses and sell non-core assets in October 2019, InnovateTech Solutions' optimization of its business structure and consolidation of resources in key growth areas, JetWing Aviation's restructuring in November 2021 for improved operational efficiency, MediaCorp's restructuring in December for operational efficiency and value enhancement, SkyQuest Airlines' merger of its leasing subsidiary with the main company, Stellar Entertainment's restructuring to optimize its business structure, improve operational efficiency, increase overall value, and enhance profitability, Sunrise Holidays' restructuring in January 2019 to optimize business structure and improve operational efficiency, various companies' divestment from non-core assets and focus on high-growth sectors such as environmental protection, healthcare technology solutions, transportation infrastructure, and others. In summary, asset restructuring has been a common practice among these entities aimed at improving their operations, reducing costs, increasing value for shareholders, and optimizing business structures in key growth areas.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-649bd1884762aea2938b30832b8e8be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed9320c543096ae4f050f033cf8f163d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be21f15c08b154a412a9d214289fb8f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-660482628b52feee928ad6cf011c5f50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55c20f91ba49a43229335e5bc34ae99a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89db1088d92f24c9800329e845aeadb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bc3f0fc44d1e5b7b92e36253c0960c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7195ba70a1b3cc863c9d69b3cc6f46d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74a3c9fcad6f9ce54f04904972f278aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0ea8bac21411453a5575bd697dc81f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09bd46ca13b030e394724af6ad225515&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e863ed97b54c4fcc9ab76db023dc0f36&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4258f3d3ee2c284dd02568acbbdc3931&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2013c7c4dbf8ad6c8740b0cd2d516da7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5fdbb05ac262b69b16c82df8838d7b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8adc4ba12676f8326423ac6fd4b55ae0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70103c00a509a0e0e16b8c7f9c2766b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a554dcacbbbf8ca6a38364ecaf904a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8105a2621d49530c5fc80333fd22b12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3ff6087189873f42c139866ba9963a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f05f07e83cce98e4e031a0740484698b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7483c38e27a322148a263f35e16b4de6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cdc7eda8c59dae569e4befb2f047dccd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e7a773e3c15deb40ebfcaff777e4ddc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e206ba06695a7fb4f62b671c4928950&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-304dc2c6fe4dbb6da5e8de7ab2abd682&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3aca3568309a845f7609c9511ac0b07d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-121f128e1c296fdbdcb2ac8023ef9586&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2a383974edecfee1a47835a1d1f5159</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 68}]</data>
</node>
