  <data key="d1">Cash flow amounted to $50 million reflecting efficient management of activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash flow for the year, including total cash inflows and outflows, was $10 million.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash flow influenced by operating activities, investment activities, and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash flow measures the movement of cash and cash equivalents into and out of a company, JetWing Aviation's case.&lt;SEP&gt;Cash flow measures the movement of cash into and out of a company's operations.&lt;SEP&gt;Hudson Consumer Goods Co.'s cash flow for the year amounted to $100 million.&lt;SEP&gt;Refers to the net change in cash and cash equivalents over a specific period, influenced by operating, investing, and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The cash flow for the year amounted to $800 million, influenced by operating, investment, and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The company achieved a cash flow of $50 million.&lt;SEP&gt;The company generated a cash flow of $300 million.&lt;SEP&gt;The company generated a cash flow of $50 million from operating, investment, and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The company generated a cash flow of $80 million due to operating activities, investment activities, and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The company generated a cash flow of $80 million, resulting from its operating activities, investment activities, and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The company generated significant cash flow, indicating strong financial performance and effective management of investment and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The company reported a cash flow of $250 million for the accounting period.&lt;SEP&gt;The company's cash flow amounted to $100 million.&lt;SEP&gt;The company's cash flow amounted to $18 million, resulting from its operating activities, investment activities, and financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The company's cash flow for 2020 was $100 million, influenced by operating activities, investment activities, and financing activities.&lt;SEP