anization that formed strategic partnerships with schools to integrate its educational programs and expand its physical learning centers.&lt;SEP&gt;EduCorp is an organization that has implemented policies for fairness and compliance in all related transactions.)"&lt;SEP&gt;EduCorp is an organization that maintains a robust internal control system and assesses its effectiveness regularly.&lt;SEP&gt;EduCorp is an organization that promotes a culture of integrity and ethical behavior by conducting mandatory ethics training for all employees.&lt;SEP&gt;EduCorp is an organization that underwent debt restructuring in March 2020 to optimize its capital structure.&lt;SEP&gt;EduCorp is an organization with specified debt ratios.&lt;SEP&gt;EduCorp is an organization with total assets amounting to $500 million at the end of the accounting period.</data>
