<node id="SPINE">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">The spine, also known as the vertebral column, consists of the cervical, thoracic, lumbar, sacral, and coccygeal regions. It serves as a crucial structural support system for the body and protects the spinal cord. In various assessments and examinations of patient Q. Gomez, the spine was found to exhibit normal curvature without any deformities or tenderness. The physical examination also showed no abnormalities in the spine, confirming its proper alignment and function. Overall, the spine health is assessed as being within normal parameters during comprehensive medical evaluations.</data>
