<node id="LIMBS">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">The comprehensive summary for the entities LIMBS indicates that they refer to the arms and legs, which are crucial for mobility and movement across various planes of motion. The limbs were assessed during examinations for patient Q. Gomez, revealing normal muscle tone, strength, absence of edema, and full range of motion with no deformities or tenderness. The limbs demonstrated a complete range of motion without contractures and showed signs of healthy circulation in the extremities, as indicated by peripheral cyanosis but no edema detected. In some cases, limited range of motion due to pain was observed over specific areas like the left femur, while other assessments confirmed normal movement and functionality of the limbs. Overall, the limbs were described as being within normal limits with respect to strength, tone, edema, and range of motion.</data>
