<node id="NERVOUS SYSTEM">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A comprehensive assessment of the nervous system was conducted on individuals Q. Gomez and H. Flores. The evaluation included a thorough examination of all cranial nerves II-XII, confirming their integrity without focal neurological deficits detected. Both patients were found to be alert and oriented with normal reflexes, motor strength, and sensory functions.

In addition, hypertonicity and limited mouth opening, as well as impaired rapid alternating movements, were observed features affecting the nervous system in these individuals. The assessment also noted a weak suck reflex for one patient.

The nervous system is responsible for transmitting signals between different parts of the body, coordinating movement and sensation, controlling various functions in the body, and responding to external stimuli.</data>
