<node id="NECK">
  <data key="d0">ORGANISM</data>
  <data key="d1">Comprehensive physical examination focused on the neck area for patient Q. Gomez.&lt;SEP&gt;Goiter present, thyroid enlarged and tender area identified during examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Inspection of the neck region, including jugular vein distention and softness. No enlargement or signs of obstruction were detected, suggesting normal lymphatic drainage and vascular health in this area.&lt;SEP&gt;Performed as part of a comprehensive physical examination for patient Q. Gomez, focusing on the neck area.&lt;SEP&gt;Refers to examination of the neck area, described as supple with no masses present.&lt;SEP&gt;Refers to the neck as an organ system involved in the systematic examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Supple neck with no masses was noted as part of the systematic examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Supple with no masses or gland enlargement noted.&lt;SEP&gt;The neck region was examined for masses or other issues.&lt;SEP&gt;The neck was examined for suppleness, masses, or bruits as part of the systematic assessment; findings included no masses or bruit and normal supple consistency.&lt;SEP&gt;The neck was examined for suppleness, masses, or bruits as part of the systematic assessment; findings included no masses or bruit and normal supple consistency."&lt;SEP&gt;The neck was found to have a normal range of motion and no masses or tenderness were detected.&lt;SEP&gt;The neck was noted to be supple with no masses or tenderness.&lt;SEP&gt;The neck was noted to have normal range of motion with no masses in the systematic examination.&lt;SEP&gt;The physical examination findings for the neck area include swelling on the left side and limited mobility due to a lump.&lt;SEP&gt;The region between the head and the torso, containing various structures including lymph nodes, thyroid gland, and trachea.&lt;SEP&gt;The region from the shoulders to the top of the chest which was described as supple with no thyromegaly.</data>
