<node id="ABDOMEN">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">Abdomen: The abdomen is described as soft, non-tender, and free from notable abnormalities or organomegaly in multiple descriptions provided for various patients, including Q. Gomez. It was also noted during systematic examinations that no palpable liver or spleen were present, indicating a normal abdominal cavity without underlying pathologies. No specific instances of tenderness or enlargement (hepatosplenomegaly) were observed in any of the descriptions. The region below the chest containing vital internal organs such as the stomach, liver, and intestines was also examined for tenderness or other issues during these systematic examinations.</data>
