<node id="RECTUM AND ANUS">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">The comprehensive examination data provided covers various entities related to the rectum and anus, including patients I. Chavez at Yorkshire General Hospital, Q. Gomez at several hospitals, E. Parker at Cameron General Hospital, and E. Cruz at an unspecified hospital. The descriptions indicate that no examinations were performed for these individuals in certain instances, with the absence of examination noted multiple times. In cases where examinations were conducted, they revealed normal findings without any abnormalities detected in the rectum or anus areas. These areas are part of the gastrointestinal tract responsible for storing feces until expulsion from the body and were described as normal during visual inspections when examined.</data>
