<node id="MASTOIDITIS">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A condition characterized by inflammation of the mastoid bone in the temporal region, often caused by an infection spreading from the middle ear.&lt;SEP&gt;An infection and inflammation of the mastoid bone behind the ears.&lt;SEP&gt;Inflammation of the mastoid bone in the skull, often resulting from a bacterial infection.&lt;SEP&gt;Mastoiditis is a condition characterized by swelling, redness, significant tenderness, collapse with purulent discharge, cloudy air cells, and a presenting cloudy appearance.&lt;SEP&gt;Mastoiditis is an infection of the mastoid bone, often treated in hospitals like Cameron General Hospital.</data>
