<edge source="ACUTE ANGLE-CLOSURE GLUOAMA" target="DIAGNOSTIC BASIS">
  <data key="d4">72.0</data>
  <data key="d5">The diagnosis was based on a history of sudden vision change, eye pain, elevated intraocular pressure, visual field loss, and examination findings.&lt;SEP&gt;The examination findings, including the lack of photophobia and discharge, helped rule out other conditions such as acute iridocyclitis and conjunctivitis.&lt;SEP&gt;The measurement of elevated intraocular pressure supports the diagnosis.&lt;SEP&gt;The patient exhibited symptoms such as sudden vision change, eye pain, elevated intraocular pressure, visual field loss, and specific examination findings ruling out other conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;The presence of eye pain further supports the diagnosis.&lt;SEP&gt;The presence of eye pain, elevated intraocular pressure, and visual field loss supports the diagnosis.&lt;SEP&gt;The presence of visual field loss supports the diagnosis.&lt;SEP&gt;The ruling out of other systemic conditions confirmed the primary diagnosis of acute angle-closure glaucoma.</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-c8f4aadc4dd9cc2b2c40802327c818b0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
